--------------------------- RESUME GAME HERE -----------------------
The garrison is alive with cautious celebration. Soldiers share rations and stories of the surge—the way the ground screamed, the moment the pressure lifted. A few glance your way with something between wariness and respect. Word has spread: the tiefling broke the Ossuary.
Seren sits on an overturned crate near the stables, cleaning her bow. She looks tired but satisfied. "That's twice now I've followed you into something that should have killed us." She doesn't sound like she's complaining.
Mirren stands apart, watching the soldiers with an expression you can't quite read. She still wears the ash-grey cloak—Circle colors—but the sigil has been torn off. The edges are ragged where she ripped it free.
Aykiyeer is invisible, perched somewhere nearby. You can feel his presence—a faint warmth, a whisper of sulfur.
In your hand, the resin-encased leaf catches the fading light. Varith's gift. Her message: The Root remembers.
Lieutenant Kael approaches, boots crunching on gravel. "Word just came in. Commander Varith is returning to the garrison. She'll be here within the hour." She pauses, studying you. "She wants to speak with you personally."
Behind her, a runner is already preparing fresh horses for the Commander's escort.
The leaf-mark beneath your skin pulses once—warm, steady.
The Sleeper dreams.
The Circle is broken.
And somewhere in the distance, the Iron Root stands silent, waiting.

